HEADWORD: Corridor train
<hw>Cor"ri*dor train</hw>. <def>A train whose coaches are connected so
as to have through its entire length a continuous corridor, into which
the compartments open.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

